Yaman (archaic)

From Arabic اَلْيَمَن (al-yaman), from Proto-Semitic *yamīn- (“right; right hand”).

IPA(key): /ˈjɛ.mən/

(pin–pen merger) IPA(key): /ˈjɪ.mən/

Audio (US):

Rhymes: -ɛmən

Yemen

A country in Western Asia, in the Middle East. Official name: Republic of Yemen. Capital: Sanaa.

(historical) A region in the southern Arabian Peninsula; the Arabia Felix.

The country is traditionally referred to with the definite article the, though this construction has declined in use.[1]
